FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - TURKEY
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Foot & mouth disease, bovine - Iran 991002214836
Foot & mouth disease - Iraq 990202174036
Foot & mouth disease - Iraq (06) 990504234427
Foot & mouth disease - Israel 990124000231
Foot & mouth disease - Jordan 990308224415
Foot & mouth disease - Europe: threat 990412220906
Source: OIE 5 Nov 1999 Vol. 12 - No. 43
http://www.oie.int/info/AIS_18.HTM

Virus type Asia 1
*******************************
(Date of last previously reported outbreak of FMD virus type Asia 1
in Turkey: 1973).
*******************************
Emergency report
-----------------------
Text of a fax received on 2 November 1999 from Dr HÃ¼seyin
Sungur, General Director of Protection and Control, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Affairs, Ankara:
Report date: 2 November 1999.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 22 October 1999.
Estimated date of first infection: 18 October 1999.
Outbreaks:
Location: Eleskirt district, Agri province, eastern Anatolia
No. of outbreaks: 2
The first outbreak was diagnosed clinically on 22 October 1999 in
(iftepinar (sic) village. The disease spread to Sadakli village in
Eleskirt district on 25 October 1999.
Description of affected population: 1- to 2-year-old fattening cattle.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species bovine
susceptible 1050
cases 33
deaths 4
destroyed 0
slaughtered 29

Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Foot and Mouth
Disease Institute, Ankara.
B. Diagnostic tests used: complement fixation test and ELISA(1).
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: smuggled animals.
B. Mode of spread: contact with infected smuggled animals and
animal transportation.
Control measures during reporting period:
- control of animal movements; strict quarantine measures have
been taken;
- the surveillance system has been strengthened in eastern
Anatolia;
- modified stamping-out policy;
- ring vaccination.
(1) ELISA: enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay.
--
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Eastern Anatolia has borders with Georgia, Armenia, Iran, Iraq &
Syria -- basically Kurd country -- from any of which these cattle
could have been smuggled. See also refs. above. - Mod.JW
